data.name: Roasted Red Pepper Dip
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and flavorful dip made with roasted red peppers, perfect for parties or a snack.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a blender or food processor, combine the roasted red peppers, cream cheese, garlic, lemon juice, and olive oil.
Blend until smooth and creamy. If the dip is too thick, you can add a little water or more olive oil to reach your desired consistency.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Transfer the dip to a serving bowl and garnish with chopped fresh parsley if desired.
Serve with pita chips, crackers, or fresh veggies.
data.modifiersForBase: Creamy and flavorful with a hint of garlic
